0:{"buildId":"I3GEKSVLVTWqxcEXDRaWq","rsc":["$","$1","c",{"children":[["$","article",null,{"className":"min-h-screen bg-white","children":["$","div",null,{"className":"max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-12","children":[["$","header",null,{"className":"mb-8","children":[["$","h1",null,{"className":"text-4xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4","children":"How implementation of ISO 14001 EMS can reduce Energy Consumption?"}],["$","div",null,{"className":"flex items-center gap-4 text-gray-600","children":[["$","time",null,{"dateTime":"2026-01-02T06:31:56+00:00","children":"January 2, 2026"}],["$","span",null,{"className":"inline-block px-3 py-1 bg-blue-100 text-blue-800 rounded-full text-sm","children":"general"}]]}]]}],null,["$","div",null,{"className":"mb-8 p-4 bg-gray-50 rounded-lg border-l-4 border-blue-500","children":["$","p",null,{"className":"text-gray-700 italic","children":"Check out implementation of ISO 14001 EMS can reduce Energy Consumption and its costs pertaining especially to electricity, natural gas and water consumption"}]}],["$","div",null,{"className":"prose prose-lg max-w-none mb-8 text-gray-700 leading-relaxed","children":[["$","p","0",{"className":"mb-6 text-justify leading-8","children":"How implementation of ISO 14001 EMS can reduce Energy Consumption?"}],["$","p","1",{"className":"mb-6 text-justify leading-8","children":"ISO 14001 EMS certification is one of the most sought and most preferred environmental standard and for the several organizations who have obtained this ISO certification, its impact of processes and methodologies on the environment is quite important. There are few fundamental advantages that ISO 14001 EMS certification will bring, corresponding to financial or monetary savings on utility bills such as electricity, water or gas. Often, people tend to keep in mind that, even approximately two decades ago, the need to drive internal business energy efficiencies and economize was the main driving force for several businesses to become certified to the ISO 14001 EMS standard. Therefore, how can today’s ISO 14001 EMS certified businesses ensure that they will understand the monetary and economic advantages of reduced energy consumptions and their bills?"}],["$","p","2",{"className":"mb-6 text-justify leading-8","children":"How ISO 14001 EMS implementation will help?"}],["$","p","3",{"className":"mb-6 text-justify leading-8","children":"Section 6 of the ISO 14001 EMS standard highlight the idea of “planning,” and plenty of organization nominate energy consumption as either an environmental facet to be maintained and scaled back or maybe a part of an environmental objective, looking on the dimensions and context of a certain organization. Regardless of how your organization decides to cope with it, the utilization of gas, electricity and water are often very valuable and expensive at the same time to business and clearly a drain on the Earth’s resources."}],["$","p","4",{"className":"mb-6 text-justify leading-8","children":"Reducing Energy consumption by splitting utilities"}],["$","p","5",{"className":"mb-6 text-justify leading-8","children":"Almost all types of organizations consume energy in the form of water, electricity or gas or even three forms of energy. In most cases, particularly in large scale organizations with larger usage, it should make sense to separate or split these utilities apart to make sure they will be controlled as efficiently and effectively as possible."}],["$","p","6",{"className":"mb-6 text-justify leading-8","children":"Let us delve into the detail and see how to accomplish it."}],"$L2","$L3","$L4","$L5","$L6","$L7","$L8","$L9","$La","$Lb","$Lc","$Ld","$Le","$Lf","$L10","$L11","$L12","$L13"]}],"$L14"]}]}],["$L15"],"$L16"]}],"loading":null,"isPartial":false}
2:["$","p","7",{"className":"mb-6 text-justify leading-8","children":"Electricity"}]
3:["$","p","8",{"className":"mb-6 text-justify leading-8","children":"This is an inevitable need for several modern businesses and it is a significant cost. By implementing the recent ISO 14001 EMS standard with a small business, we found that over 40% of the business’s electricity bills were increased outside of business hours. This could give a business with real motivation and stimulus to cut back those costs. The only solution to scaling back the costs can be accomplished with good judgment and technological factors. Here are some tips:"}]
4:["$","p","9",{"className":"mb-6 text-justify leading-8","children":"Use Signs: Devising signboard could be really helpful. Signboards such as Turn off the lights when the area is not in use. These signboards are old school but it is very effective. Proper communication with the team jotting down the targets and objective of such an initiative, and how everyone’s behaviour will contribute, commonly bring immediate enhancements."}]
5:["$","p","10",{"className":"mb-6 text-justify leading-8","children":"Delegate Employees:In some cases, designating a liable or accountable person, or employees will provide your workers with a degree of contact if they have additional data or have queries on how to facilitate to save electricity."}]
6:["$","p","11",{"className":"mb-6 text-justify leading-8","children":"Making use of Smart technology:Latest technological solutions may also facilitate in saving electricity. Make sure all the sensors are accurate and used, contemplate remote temperature management applications, think about LED and sensor lighting in your workplace, you can also consider the chance of POE (Power over Ethernet) lighting systems, wherever low consumption electricity can be transmitted over LAN cables to supply an intelligent and sensor-led lighting solution for your workplace. This smart technology is sure to play a significant part in reducing electricity consumption for businesses in the upcoming years."}]
7:["$","p","12",{"className":"mb-6 text-justify leading-8","children":"Natural Gas Consumption"}]
8:["$","p","13",{"className":"mb-6 text-justify leading-8","children":"Whether gas or heating fuel, most workplaces need some form of heating. There are many easy and straightforward questions you will be able to raise to make sure your system is economical and costs are maintained to a minimum:"}]
9:["$","p","14",{"className":"mb-6 text-justify leading-8","children":"How frequently your systems are serviced"}]
a:["$","p","15",{"className":"mb-6 text-justify leading-8","children":"Are temperature controls and sensors operating and used?"}]
b:["$","p","16",{"className":"mb-6 text-justify leading-8","children":"Is the heating plant set to ensure that there is no out of hours use, except in times of extraordinarily low temperatures which might bring a risk of a frozen system?"}]
c:["$","p","17",{"className":"mb-6 text-justify leading-8","children":"Knowing these things in your business with regular reviews and actions will assist you to know this impact/cost and scale back it consequently. Once more, addressing these objectives to your workers can bring immediate advantages in terms of raising their awareness and ever-changing behaviour, and sometimes in terms of welcoming feedback and suggestions."}]
d:["$","p","18",{"className":"mb-6 text-justify leading-8","children":"Water Consumption"}]
e:["$","p","19",{"className":"mb-6 text-justify leading-8","children":"Water is one of the most crucial elements in Earth for nurturing life and growth on this planet. Conserving water resource should be of predominant importance to every single individual on this planet. Each business and family will play a part in this, and even the simplest of measures will be effective. For several workers, hearing about the importance of an initiative from the organizational leaders will greater impact on workers and on their day to day tasks, and results tend to follow. Again, a combination of strategies will facilitate to scale back your company’s water consumption:"}]
f:["$","p","20",{"className":"mb-6 text-justify leading-8","children":"Ensure your system is maintained and has no leaks"}]
10:["$","p","21",{"className":"mb-6 text-justify leading-8","children":"Ensure signs are present to emphasize the importance of preserving water"}]
11:["$","p","22",{"className":"mb-6 text-justify leading-8","children":"Consider sensor installed taps to control the quantity of water discharged"}]
12:["$","p","23",{"className":"mb-6 text-justify leading-8","children":"Review and communicate your water usage frequently to get suggestions and retain focus."}]
13:["$","p","24",{"className":"mb-6 text-justify leading-8","children":"Like several components pertaining to the ISO 14001 EMS certification, utilizing the “Plan, Do, Check, Act” strategy will bring positive results."}]
